text.section:
A carrier may cancel or refuse to renew a health benefit plan only:
for nonpayment of premiums;
for fraud or intentional misrepresentation of material fact by the small employer;
for noncompliance with a material plan provision relating to employer contributions or group participation rules;
when the carrier elects not to renew:
all of its health benefit plans that are issued to small employers in the State; or
the particular health benefit plan for all small employers in the State; or
in the case of a health maintenance organization, where there is no longer any enrollee who lives, resides, or works in the health maintenance organization's approved service area.
